&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Estates Carpenter&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Ashford and St Peters Hospital&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Hours: Full Time 37.5 hours per week&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Band 4 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A position has arisen for a Maintenance Craftsman Carpenter. This role significantly improves Estates ability to support our clinical services and make a real difference to the department. Applications are welcomed from suitably experienced candidates to carry out the duties of a Maintenance Craftsman Carpenter. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applications are welcomed from suitably experienced candidates to carry out the duties of a Carpenter. The successful applicant will be employed full time on a 5 day week Job Share basis. Duties include the repair and maintenance of doors and windows, installation of shelving and notice boards, key cutting, lock installation and repairs and minor refurbishments around both sites. This is an ideal job for a skilled person and available to work full time.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Duties include the repair and maintenance of Trust assets and Planned Preventative maintenance on selected equipment. The successful applicant will be based at St Peters but will be expected to work cross site, as required by the Works Officers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will be expected to work on their own initiative and prioritise work requests. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;It is anticipated and desirable that the post holder will undertake additional training and attend courses if deemed necessary. The post holder may also be required to undertake planned preventative maintenance as directed by the Works Officers or Maintenance Supervisor. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information please contact Andrew Hanney, Estates Manager on 01932 722887.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;To apply for this post, please visit NHS jobs. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
